race.comment: PERFECT RULER (1) comes here on the fresh side following a few strong performances in Kalgoorlie, jumping favourite in his latest effort over 1400m. He still has some upside being a lightly raced commodity and this trip looks ideal for him on the fresh side. Can notch up his maiden win. VAIN UNIVERSE (6) is knocking on the door of a maiden win, finishing strongly to be 1L off the winner at Kalgoorlie last time out. Cheung's 3kg claim comes in handy and a repeat of that performance out in distance will see her right in the finish. SOLASH MOON (11) is a lightly raced filly who wasn't disgraced at York last time out. Back to Maiden grade here and she carries no weight after the claim of Nottle. Can feature. QUAGMIRE (3) will find this easier and has claims from the good draw. HIGHLAND JEUNEY (10) is next best first-up.
